On Wed, 3 Feb 1999, Enbo Zhang wrote:
>Does EXT2 filesystem support files and dirs auto compress and decompress as
>MS NTFS do? or other Linux filesystem can do that?
There used to be "E2compr" (
http://debs.fuller.edu/e2compr/
), a patch to allow
transparent file compression on ext2,
and "double" (
http://perso.cybercable.fr/~verbavat/double/
), a compressed block
device driver.
I have no idea if they are updated for 2.2.x though.
                        Massimiliano Ghilardi
